 I had not much difficulty in putting those ten rude nails in order, and while doing so I kept comparing our hands: his were larger and darker; but never mind, I thought, they’ll pale by and by. As I never wore any wedding ring, all I had to add to his hand was my wristwatch. He moved his fingers, turning his wrist this way and that, very pleased.

“Now, quick. Let’s change. Take off everything, my friend, to the last stitch.”

“Ugh,” grunted Felix, “it’ll be cold.”

